er sheet.' },\\n    { stage: 'beats', label: 'Beat sheet', description: 'Store the accepted Save-the-Cat beat sheet for the session.', status: 'in_progress', detail: 'Midpoint needs one more bedtime-soft pass.' },\\n    { stage: 'story_setup', label: 'Story setup', description: 'Store soft planning targets such as word count, runtime, and chapter structure.', status: 'draft', detail: null },\\n    { stage: 'composition', label: 'Composition', description: 'Write the story durably in segments, with room for interruption and targeted rewrites.', status: 'draft', detail: null },\\n    { stage: 'audio', label: 'Audio', description: 'Configure narration settings and generate resumable audio artifacts.', status: 'draft', detail: null },\\n    { stage: 'finalize', label: 'Finalize', description: 'Read, listen, review final assets, and download exports.', status: 'draft', detail: null }\\n  ],\\n  story_brief: {\\n    id: 'brief-1',\\n    revision_number: 1,\\n    raw_brief: 'A child follows floating lanterns across a harbor and helps a shy otter guardian bring them home.',\\n    normalized_summary: 'A harbor bedtime quest where floating lanterns guide a child and an otter toward a calm reunion.'\\n  },\\n  selected_pitch: {\\n    id: 'pitch-1',\\n    generation_key: 'batch-1',\\n    pitch_index: 0,\\n    title: 'Lanterns Over Juniper Lake',\\n    logline: 'A child and an otter guardian follow drifting lanterns across the harbor to return each light before bedtime.'\\n  },\\n  selected_character_sheet: null,\\n  selected_story_setup: {\\n    id: 'setup-1',\\n    revision_number: 1,\\n    target_word_count: 1500,\\n    target_runtime_minutes: 12,\\n    chapter_count: 4,\\n    chapter_style: 'short'\\n  },\\n  active_composition_job: null,\\n  active_audio_job: null,\\n  latest_story_asset: null,\\n  latest_audio_asset: null\\n};\\n\\nconst outputDir = '/workspace/.artifacts/webapp-qa';\\nawait fs.mkdir(outputDir, { recursive: true });\\n\\nconst browser = await puppeteer.launch({\\n  executablePath: process.env.PUPPETEER_EXECUTABLE_PATH,\\n  headless: true,\\n  args: ['--no-sandbox', '--disable-setuid-sandbox']\\n});\\n\\nasync function capture(name, viewport) {\\n  const page = await browser.newPage();\\n  await page.setViewport(viewport);\\n  await page.setRequestInterception(true);\\n  page.on('request', (request) => {\\n    const url = request.url();\\n    if (url.endsWith('/api/hello')) {\\n      request.respond({ status: 200, contentType: 'application/json', body: JSON.stringify({ message: 'Hello from FastAPI\\\"'!'\\\"' }) });\\n      return;\\n    }\\n    if (url.includes('/api/v1/sessions/moonlit-harbor')) {\\n      request.respond({ status: 200, contentType: 'application/json', body: JSON.stringify(snapshot) });\\n      return;\\n    }\\n    request.continue();\\n  });\\n\\n  await page.goto('http://frontend:8566/sessions/moonlit-harbor', { waitUntil: 'networkidle2' });\\n  await page.waitForSelector('[data-testid=\\\\\\\"workspace-route\\\\\\\"]');\\n\\n  const metrics = await page.evaluate(() => {\\n    const shell = document.querySelector('[data-testid=\\\\\\\"workspace-route\\\\\\\"]');\\n    const chat = document.querySelector('.workspace-pane--chat');\\n    const canvas = document.querySelector('.workspace-pane--canvas');\\n\\n    if (\\n      shell instanceof HTMLElement &&\\n      chat instanceof HTMLElement &&\\n      canvas instanceof HTMLElement\\n    ) {\\n      const shellRect = shell.getBoundingClientRect();\\n      const chatRect = chat.getBoundingClientRect();\\n      const canvasRect = canvas.getBoundingClientRect();\\n\\n      return {\\n        shellWidth: Math.round(shellRect.width),\\n        chatWidth: Math.round(chatRect.width),\\n        canvasWidth: Math.round(canvasRect.width),\\n        chatRatio: Number((chatRect.width / shellRect.width).toFixed(3)),\\n        isStacked:\\n          chatRect.top < canvasRect.top &&\\n          Math.abs(chatRect.left - canvasRect.left) < 4,\\n      };\\n    }\\n\\n    return null;\\n  });\\n\\n  const path = \\\"'`${outputDir}/${name}.png`;\\n  await page.screenshot({ path, fullPage: true });\\n  await page.close();\\n  return { path, metrics };\\n}\\n\\nconst desktop = await capture('\\\"'prompt-22-workspace-desktop', {\\n  width: 1440,\\n  height: 900,\\n});\\nconst mobile = await capture('prompt-22-workspace-mobile', {\\n  width: 390,\\n  height: 844,\\n});\\n\\nawait browser.close();\\nconsole.log(JSON.stringify({ desktop, mobile }, null, 2));\\nEOF\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"\",\"exit_code\":null,\"status\":\"in_progress\"}}\n./prompts/22-workspace-two-pane-layout.codex.jsonlines:154:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_82\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/bin/zsh -lc \\\"docker compose -f infra/compose/docker-compose.yml run --rm --no-deps browser node --input-type=module - <<'EOF'\\nimport fs from 'node:fs/promises';\\nimport puppeteer from 'puppeteer';\\n\\nconst snapshot = {\\n  id: 'moonlit-harbor',\\n  display_title: 'Lanterns Over Juniper Lake',\\n  working_title: 'Lanterns Over Juniper Lake',\\n  current_stage: 'beats',\\n  resume_stage: 'beats',\\n  furthest_completed_stage: 'characters',\\n  overall_status: 'in_progress',\\n  created_at: '2026-04-01T03:00:00Z',\\n  updated_at: '2026-04-01T05:15:00Z',\\n  completed_at: null,\\n  selected_genre: { id: 'genre-1', slug: 'quest-fantasy', label: 'Quest Fantasy' },\\n  selected_tone_profile: { id: 'tone-1', slug: 'hushed-wonder', label: 'Hushed Wonder' },\\n  progress: { total_stages: 10, completed_stages: 5, in_progress_stages: 1, needs_regeneration_stages: 0 },\\n  stage_states: [\\n    { stage: 'genre', label: 'Genre', description: 'Choose the overall bedtime-story lane before the rest of the plan is shaped.', status: 'completed', detail: 'Accepted quest fantasy.' },\\n    { stage: 'tone', label: 'Tone', description: 'Choose the emotional texture and bedtime-safety posture for the session.', status: 'completed', detail: 'Selected a soft adventurous tone.' },\\n    { stage: 'brief', label: 'Story brief', description: \\\\\\\"Capture the user's free-form idea and any normalized planning summary derived from it.\\\\\\\", status: 'completed', detail: 'Accepted normalized brief.' },\\n    { stage: 'pitches', label: 'Pitches', description: 'Generate, compare, refine, and accept candidate story directions.', status: 'completed', detail: 'Accepted the harbor lantern pitch.' },\\n    { stage: 'characters', label: 'Characters', description: 'Define the accepted character sheet that later planning and writing will reference.', status: 'completed', detail: 'Locked the character sheet.' },\\n    { stage: 'beats', label: 'Beat sheet', description: 'Store the accepted Save-the-Cat beat sheet for the session.', status: 'in_progress', detail: 'Midpoint needs one more bedtime-soft pass.' },\\n    { stage: 'story_setup', label: 'Story setup', description: 'Store soft planning targets such as word count, runtime, and chapter structure.', status: 'draft', detail: null },\\n    { stage: 'composition', label: 'Composition', description: 'Write the story durably in segments, with room for interruption and targeted rewrites.', status: 'draft', detail: null },\\n    { stage: 'audio', label: 'Audio', description: 'Configure narration settings and generate resumable audio artifacts.', status: 'draft', detail: null },\\n    { stage: 'finalize', label: 'Finalize', description: 'Read, listen, review final assets, and download exports.', status: 'draft', detail: null }\\n  ],\\n  story_brief: {\\n    id: 'brief-1',\\n    revision_number: 1,\\n    raw_brief: 'A child follows floating lanterns across a harbor and helps a shy otter guardian bring them home.',\\n    normalized_summary: 'A harbor bedtime quest where floating lanterns guide a child and an otter toward a calm reunion.'\\n  },\\n  selected_pitch: {\\n    id: 'pitch-1',\\n    generation_key: 'batch-1',\\n    pitch_index: 0,\\n    title: 'Lanterns Over Juniper Lake',\\n    logline: 'A child and an otter guardian follow drifting lanterns across the harbor to return each light before bedtime.'\\n  },\\n  selected_character_sheet: null,\\n  selected_story_setup: {\\n    id: 'setup-1',\\n    revision_number: 1,\\n    target_word_count: 1500,\\n    target_runtime_minutes: 12,\\n    chapter_count: 4,\\n    chapter_style: 'short'\\n  },\\n  active_composition_job: null,\\n  active_audio_job: null,\\n  latest_story_asset: null,\\n  latest_audio_asset: null\\n};\\n\\nconst outputDir = '/workspace/.artifacts/webapp-qa';\\nawait fs.mkdir(outputDir, { recursive: true });\\n\\nconst browser = await puppeteer.launch({\\n  executablePath: process.env.PUPPETEER_EXECUTABLE_PATH,\\n  headless: true,\\n  args: ['--no-sandbox', '--disable-setuid-sandbox']\\n});\\n\\nasync function capture(name, viewport) {\\n  const page = await browser.newPage();\\n  await page.setViewport(viewport);\\n  await page.setRequestInterception(true);\\n  page.on('request', (request) => {\\n    const url = request.url();\\n    if (url.endsWith('/api/hello')) {\\n      request.respond({ status: 200, contentType: 'application/json', body: JSON.stringify({ message: 'Hello from FastAPI\\\"'!'\\\"' }) });\\n      return;\\n    }\\n    if (url.includes('/api/v1/sessions/moonlit-harbor')) {\\n      request.respond({ status: 200, contentType: 'application/json', body: JSON.stringify(snapshot) });\\n      return;\\n    }\\n    request.continue();\\n  });\\n\\n  await page.goto('http://frontend:8566/sessions/moonlit-harbor', { waitUntil: 'networkidle2' });\\n  await page.waitForSelector('[data-testid=\\\\\\\"workspace-route\\\\\\\"]');\\n\\n  const metrics = await page.evaluate(() => {\\n    const shell = document.querySelector('[data-testid=\\\\\\\"workspace-route\\\\\\\"]');\\n    const chat = document.querySelector('.workspace-pane--chat');\\n    const canvas = document.querySelector('.workspace-pane--canvas');\\n\\n    if (\\n      shell instanceof HTMLElement &&\\n      chat instanceof HTMLElement &&\\n      canvas instanceof HTMLElement\\n    ) {\\n      const shellRect = shell.getBoundingClientRect();\\n      const chatRect = chat.getBoundingClientRect();\\n      const canvasRect = canvas.getBoundingClientRect();\\n\\n      return {\\n        shellWidth: Math.round(shellRect.width),\\n        chatWidth: Math.round(chatRect.width),\\n        canvasWidth: Math.round(canvasRect.width),\\n        chatRatio: Number((chatRect.width / shellRect.width).toFixed(3)),\\n        isStacked:\\n          chatRect.top < canvasRect.top &&\\n          Math.abs(chatRect.left - canvasRect.left) < 4,\\n      };\\n    }\\n\\n    return null;\\n  });\\n\\n  const path = \\\"'`${outputDir}/${name}.png`;\\n  await page.screenshot({ path, fullPage: true });\\n  await page.close();\\n  return { path, metrics };\\n}\\n\\nconst desktop = await capture('\\\"'prompt-22-workspace-desktop', {\\n  width: 1440,\\n  height: 900,\\n});\\nconst mobile = await capture('prompt-22-workspace-mobile', {\\n  width: 390,\\n  height: 844,\\n});\\n\\nawait browser.close();\\nconsole.log(JSON.stringify({ desktop, mobile }, null, 2));\\nEOF\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"{\\n  \\\"desktop\\\": {\\n    \\\"path\\\": \\\"/workspace/.artifacts/webapp-qa/prompt-22-workspace-desktop.png\\\",\\n    \\\"metrics\\\": {\\n      \\\"shellWidth\\\": 1180,\\n      \\\"chatWidth\\\": 387,\\n      \\\"canvasWidth\\\": 773,\\n      \\\"chatRatio\\\": 0.328,\\n      \\\"isStacked\\\": false\\n    }\\n  },\\n  \\\"mobile\\\": {\\n    \\\"path\\\": \\\"/workspace/.artifacts/webapp-qa/prompt-22-workspace-mobile.png\\\",\\n    \\\"metrics\\\": {\\n      \\\"shellWidth\\\": 358,\\n      \\\"chatWidth\\\": 358,\\n      \\\"canvasWidth\\\": 358,\\n      \\\"chatRatio\\\": 1,\\n      \\\"isStacked\\\": true\\n    }\\n  }\\n}\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\n./prompts/22-workspace-two-pane-layout.codex.jsonlines:169:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_91\",\"type\":\"agent_message\",\"text\":\"I\u2019ve got everything needed for the reviewer summary: scope, exact verification results, screenshot paths, and the environment blockers I hit. The next and final file operation is writing `prompts/22-workspace-two-pane-layout.summary.md`.\"}}\n./prompts/31-intent-parser-service.yolopilot.jsonlines:12:{\"color\": \"cyan\", \"emoji\": \"\\ud83d\\udee0\\ufe0f\", \"event_type\": \"Command Finished\", \"message\": \"completed, exit 0: /bin/zsh -lc 'rg -n \\\"Gemini|intent|event log|EventLog|stage context|chat\\\" backend frontend docs prompts -S'\", \"raw_event\": {\"item\": {\"aggregated_output\": \"backend/README.md:42:For local development, copy the repository-root example file and add a Gemini key:\\nbackend/README.md:48:The settings module merges built-in defaults, `secrets.yaml`, and then `STORYTELLER_*` environment variables. Environment variables win when both sources set the same field. The backend-only Gemini key lives in `secrets.yaml` or the backend process environment and is never sent to the browser.\\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.tsx:16:import { SessionChatPane } from '../../features/session/chat/SessionChatPane.tsx'\\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.tsx:21:} from '../../features/session/chat/sessionChat.ts'\\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.tsx:270:    return 'This panel is intentionally preview-only until the session reaches this later step.'\\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.tsx:433:  const chatMessages = useSessionChatMessages()\\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.tsx:448:    if (snapshot == null || chatMessages.length > 0) {\\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.tsx:454:    chatMessages.length,\\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.tsx:495:  const chatActivityState = buildChatActivityState(\\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.tsx:576:        <aside className=\\\"panel workspace-pane workspace-pane--chat\\\">\\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.tsx:578:            activityLabel={chatActivityState.activityLabel}\\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.tsx:583:            disabledReason={chatActivityState.disabledReason}\\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.tsx:584:            isBusy={chatActivityState.isBusy}\\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.tsx:585:            messages={chatMessages}\\nprompts/00-project-charter.codex.jsonlines:9:{\\\"type\\\":\\\"item.completed\\\",\\\"item\\\":{\\\"id\\\":\\\"item_3\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"command_execution\\\",\\\"command\\\":\\\"/bin/zsh -lc \\\\\\\"rg --files -g 'README.md' -g 'docs/**' -g 'prompts/**' -g 'AGENTS.md'\\\\\\\"\\\",\\\"aggregated_output\\\":\\\"prompts/00-project-charter.codex.jsonlines\\\\nprompts/36-conversation-memory-summaries.md\\\\nprompts/99-release-checklist-and-future-roadmap.md\\\\nprompts/44-pitch-generation-pipeline.md\\\\nprompts/42-story-setup-brief-form.md\\\\nprompts/07-developer-bootstrap-scripts.md\\\\nprompts/20-frontend-app-shell-and-routing.md\\\\nprompts/52-bedtime-safety-and-content-guidelines.md\\\\nprompts/02-vite-react-scaffold.md\\\\nprompts/78-download-endpoints-and-object-access.md\\\\nprompts/01-monorepo-skeleton.md\\\\nprompts/13-storage-abstraction-and-buckets.md\\\\nprompts/48-save-the-cat-beat-sheet-generation.md\\\\nprompts/95-ci-pipeline.md\\\\nprompts/46-character-sheet-generation.md\\\\nprompts/83-artifact-packaging-and-links.md\\\\nprompts/11-postgres-schema-and-migrations.md\\\\nprompts/06-gitignore-and-secrets-hygiene.md\\\\nprompts/65-interrupt-and-redirect-composition.md\\\\nprompts/30-chat-to-ui-action-schema.md\\\\nprompts/37-agent-tool-registry.md\\\\nprompts/54-chapter-scene-card-editor.md\\\\nprompts/62-composition-streaming-events.md\\\\nprompts/26-main-pane-stage-scaffold.md\\\\nprompts/56-revision-history-and-branches.md\\\\nprompts/00-project-charter.md\\\\nprompts/88-artifact-retention-and-cleanup.md\\\\nprompts/63-composition-main-pane-ui.md\\\\nprompts/74-background-music-mixing.md\\\\nprompts/14-repositories-and-session-service.md\\\\nprompts/61-segmented-writing-engine.md\\\\nprompts/67-diff-and-compare-ui.md\\\\nprompts/17-realtime-event-schema.md\\\\nprompts/90-local-identity-and-future-auth-shape.md\\\\nprompts/80-finalize-screen-read-and-listen.md\\\\nprompts/45-pitch-refinement-via-chat.md\\\\nprompts/92-observability-and-logging.md\\\\nprompts/72-narration-segmentation.md\\\\nprompts/04-docker-compose-foundation.md\\\\nprompts/64-agent-summary-messages-during-composition.md\\\\nprompts/41-tone-selection-api-and-ui.md\\\\nprompts/23-frontend-state-foundation.md\\\\nprompts/97-security-review.md\\\\nprompts/12-seed-genres-and-tones.md\\\\nprompts/81-docx-export-pipeline.md\\\\nprompts/87-developer-debug-inspector.md\\\\nprompts/25-chat-window-foundation.md\\\\nprompts/60-composition-job-orchestration.md\\\\nprompts/96-compose-dev-and-prod-shapes.md\\\\nprompts/49-beat-sheet-refinement-ui-and-chat.md\\\\nprompts/93-accessibility-pass-and-keyboard-support.md\\\\nprompts/15-event-log-and-audit-trail.md\\\\nprompts/47-character-refinement-via-chat.md\\\\nprompts/16-asset-metadata-and-file-records.md\\\\nprompts/76-audio-preview-and-segment-status-ui.md\\\\nprompts/53-outline-drill-down.md\\\\nprompts/66-rewrite-prior-segments.md\\\\nprompts/18-postgres-job-runner-skeleton.md\\\\nprompts/43-brief-normalization-service.md\\\\nprompts/base_prompt.md\\\\nprompts/50-story-length-duration-and-chapter-setup.md\\\\nprompts/86-completed-session-summary-and-search.md\\\\nprompts/82-html-markdown-and-reader-formatting.md\\\\nprompts/77-final-audio-assembly.md\\\\nprompts/79-audio-pipeline-tests.md\\\\nprompts/34-ui-events-to-agent-context.md\\\\nprompts/89-full-journey-e2e-test.md\\\\nprompts/57-composition-prompt-assembly.md\\\\nprompts/39-bridge-and-replay-tests.md\\\\nprompts/03-fastapi-scaffold.md\\\\nprompts/31-intent-parser-service.md\\\\nprompts/75-audio-job-orchestration.md\\\\nprompts/00-project-charter.yolopilot.md\\\\nprompts/85-audio-player-with-text-sync-hooks.md\\\\nprompts/05-backend-settings-and-secrets-loading.md\\\\nprompts/33-action-echoes-in-chat.md\\\\nprompts/08-repo-quality-tooling.md\\\\nprompts/19-data-layer-integration-tests.md\\\\nprompts/73-gemini-tts-integration.md\\\\nprompts/71-audio-length-estimation.md\\\\nprompts/22-workspace-two-pane-layout.md\\\\nprompts/38-session-replay-and-resume-hydration.md\\\\nprompts/10-domain-model-and-state-machine.md\\\\nprompts/40-genre-selection-api-and-ui.md\\\\nprompts/70-audio-settings-model-and-ui.md\\\\nprompts/69-composition-loop-e2e-test.md\\\\nprompts/00-project-charter.yolopilot.jsonlines\\\\nprompts/27-reusable-form-and-card-components.md\\\\nprompts/98-demo-data-and-onboarding.md\\\\nprompts/21-past-sessions-home-screen.md\\\\nprompts/51-correlation-heuristics.md\\\\nprompts/35-chat-commands-and-quick-actions.md\\\\nprompts/55-continuity-bible.md\\\\nprompts/28-error-loading-and-feedback-states.md\\\\nprompts/32-ui-action-policy-engine.md\\\\nprompts/94-performance-pass.md\\\\nprompts/29-frontend-websocket-client-skeleton.md\\\\nprompts/58-usage-cost-and-latency-metrics.md\\\\nprompts/68-autosave-drafts-and-partials.md\\\\nprompts/09-initial-system-diagram-and-adr.md\\\\nprompts/91-rate-limits-retries-and-fallbacks.md\\\\nprompts/24-design-tokens-and-accessibility-foundation.md\\\\nprompts/84-reader-ui-with-navigation.md\\\\nprompts/59-planning-funnel-e2e-test.md\\\\n\\\",\\\"exit_code\\\":0,\\\"status\\\":\\\"completed\\\"}}\\nprompts/00-project-charter.codex.jsonlines:13:{\\\"type\\\":\\\"item.completed\\\",\\\"item\\\":{\\\"id\\\":\\\"item_6\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"command_execution\\\",\\\"command\\\":\\\"/bin/zsh -lc \\\\\\\"sed -n '1,220p' prompts/00-project-charter.md\\\\\\\"\\\",\\\"aggregated_output\\\":\\\"# 00 \\u2014 Project Charter and Success Criteria\\\\n\\\\nRead `base_prompt.md` first and preserve all prior prompt work.\\\\n\\\\n## Objective\\\\n\\\\nCreate the initial project framing for a full-stack app that helps a user build a bedtime story, turn it into audio, and resume past sessions.\\\\n\\\\n## Build\\\\n- Write a top-level README that explains the product vision, the end-to-end story workflow, the required stages, and the major technical choices already fixed by the brief.\\\\n- Document the non-negotiable requirements: React + Vite frontend, Python FastAPI backend, PostgreSQL for all structured data, a file-backed GCS emulator for blobs, Docker Compose for local orchestration, and `secrets.yaml` kept out of git.\\\\n- Add a short architecture note describing why all Gemini calls must happen on the backend and why long-running composition and audio jobs need resumable server-side state.\\\\n\\\\n## Deliverables\\\\n\\\\n- `README.md` with product overview and local development expectations\\\\n- `docs/product-brief.md` or equivalent design note\\\\n- `docs/architecture-overview.md` with the first cut of the system picture\\\\n\\\\n## Acceptance checks\\\\n\\\\n- A new engineer can read the repo root and understand what is being built.\\\\n- The required story stages from the brief are explicitly listed in order.\\\\n- The first screen requirement \\u2014 a past-sessions screen for resume/edit/create \\u2014 is called out early, not buried.\\\\n\\\\n## Notes\\\\n\\\\nDo not generate implementation code yet beyond lightweight documentation scaffolding.\\\\n\\\\n## Suggested commit label\\\\n\\\\n`feat(prompt-00): project charter`\\\\n\\\",\\\"exit_code\\\":0,\\\"status\\\":\\\"completed\\\"}}\\nprompts/00-project-charter.codex.jsonlines:14:{\\\"type\\\":\\\"item.completed\\\",\\\"item\\\":{\\\"id\\\":\\\"item_5\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"command_execution\\\",\\\"command\\\":\\\"/bin/zsh -lc \\\\\\\"sed -n '1,240p' prompts/base_prompt.md\\\\\\\"\\\",\\\"aggregated_output\\\":\\\"# Base Prompt \\u2014 Build the Bedtime Story + Audio App\\\\n\\\\nYou are building a production-minded local-first application that helps a user create a bedtime story from idea to finished text and finished narration audio.\\\\n\\\\nThis prompt pack is designed to be used **sequentially**. Read this file first, then work through the numbered prompts in order. Each numbered prompt should be treated as an incremental implementation task inside the same repository. Preserve prior work unless the new prompt explicitly asks you to refactor it.\\\\n\\\\n## Product Summary\\\\n\\\\nThe product is a guided story-creation studio with a persistent session model. A user should be able to:\\\\n\\\\n1. See past story sessions first, including both in-progress and completed work.\\\\n2. Open a session to resume, edit, or finalize it.\\\\n3. Use a **two-pane workspace**:\\\\n   - **Left pane:** chat window, about one-third of the desktop width.\\\\n   - **Main pane:** structured workflow UI, about two-thirds of the desktop width.\\\\n4. Control the product in **both directions**:\\\\n   - The user can type in chat, and the system can translate those messages into UI actions.\\\\n   - The user can act directly in the UI, and those actions should be reflected in the chat log and in durable session state.\\\\n5. Move through a staged workflow:\\\\n   - Genre selection\\\\n   - Tone selection\\\\n   - Story setup / free-form brief\\\\n   - Story pitches\\\\n   - Character sheet\\\\n   - Save-the-Cat beat sheet\\\\n   - Story setup preferences such as word count, runtime, and chapters\\\\n   - Composition\\\\n   - Audio configuration and audio generation\\\\n   - Finalize / read / listen / download\\\\n6. Download the final story as a **Word document** and the final narration as an audio file.\\\\n7. Read or listen inside the product UI after generation is complete.\\\\n\\\\n## Story-Generation Philosophy\\\\n\\\\nThe app is for **bedtime stories**, not generic fiction generation. That means:\\\\n\\\\n- Wonder is welcome.\\\\n- Adventure is welcome.\\\\n- Mystery is welcome.\\\\n- Tension is allowed, but it should be modulated for bedtime use.\\\\n- Emotional repair matters.\\\\n- The ending should feel safe, satisfying, and restful.\\\\n- The narration and UI tone should remain calm, readable, and trustworthy.\\\\n\\\\nUse the research docs in this prompt pack as direct product input, especially the Save The Cat notes and the curated genre/tone catalog.\\\\n\\\\n## Required Story Workflow\\\\n\\\\nThe session should support this exact conceptual flow:\\\\n\\\\n1. **Genre Selection**\\\\n   - The user selects from the curated genre list.\\\\n2. **Tone Selection**\\\\n   - The user is shown preconfigured tone options for the chosen genre.\\\\n3. **Story Setup**\\\\n   - The user provides a free-form description of the story they want to tell.\\\\n4. **Story Pitches**\\\\n   - Gemini generates multiple candidate pitches.\\\\n   - The user can select one, ask for alternatives, or refine via chat.\\\\n5. **Character Sheet**\\\\n   - Gemini generates multiple candidate character sheets.\\\\n   - The user can select or refine via chat.\\\\n6. **Story Beats**\\\\n   - Gemini generates a Save-the-Cat beat sheet for the selected plan.\\\\n   - The user can refine the beats via chat or UI.\\\\n7. **Story Setup Preferences**\\\\n   - The user can set soft planning targets such as word count, read-aloud duration, and chapter organization.\\\\n   - These are **guides**, not strict constraints.\\\\n8. **Composition**\\\\n   - The system writes in segments.\\\\n   - The UI shows a live typewriter-like experience.\\\\n   - Writing should generally appear faster than the user can comfortably read.\\\\n   - A visible progress bar should show overall story progress.\\\\n   - The agent should periodically post chat summaries of what it is writing.\\\\n   - The user can interrupt and redirect composition, including causing rewrites of prior segments.\\\\n9. **Audio**\\\\n   - The user configures voice, music, speed, and related settings.\\\\n   - The system estimates final length heuristically.\\\\n   - Audio is generated in segments with visible progress.\\\\n10. **Finalize**\\\\n   - The user can read and listen in the UI.\\\\n   - The user can download the story as a Word document and the final audio as a file.\\\\n\\\\n## Non-Negotiable Technical Requirements\\\\n\\\\n### Frontend\\\\n- React\\\\n- Vite\\\\n- TypeScript\\\\n- The browser must **never** hold provider secrets\\\\n- Chat pane on the left, main pane on the right\\\\n- Past sessions screen must be the first meaningful screen\\\\n\\\\n### Backend\\\\n- Python\\\\n- FastAPI\\\\n- Durable backend-owned business logic\\\\n- Clear separation between route handlers, domain services, AI orchestration, and persistence\\\\n\\\\n### Data and Infrastructure\\\\n- PostgreSQL is the durable store for structured application state\\\\n- Use a **file-backed GCS emulator** for object/blob storage in local development\\\\n- The app must run with Docker Compose\\\\n- Postgres and object storage must both be **persistent across restarts**\\\\n- `secrets.yaml` exists locally for API keys and must **not** be committed to git\\\\n\\\\n### AI\\\\n- Use the **Gemini 3.1 family** for text/planning/composition workloads\\\\n- Keep model IDs centralized in config, not scattered through the codebase\\\\n- Put AI calls behind backend services and adapters\\\\n- Use structured outputs wherever determinism matters\\\\n- Use separate adapters for:\\\\n  - planning/classification/intent parsing\\\\n  - long-form story generation\\\\n  - narration / TTS\\\\n- Keep narration generation isolated behind a provider-style interface because model offerings evolve\\\\n\\\\n## Recommended Architecture\\\\n\\\\nUse a calm, maintainable architecture rather than a clever one.\\\\n\\\\n### Suggested application shape\\\\n- `frontend/` \\u2014 React + Vite app\\\\n- `backend/` \\u2014 FastAPI app plus domain services\\\\n- `infra/` \\u2014 Docker Compose, Dockerfiles, local infrastructure helpers\\\\n- `docs/` \\u2014 architecture notes, ADRs, product docs\\\\n\\\\n### Suggested backend layers\\\\n- `api/` or route handlers\\\\n- `settings/`\\\\n- `db/`\\\\n- `models/`\\\\n- `repositories/`\\\\n- `services/`\\\\n- `worker/`\\\\n- `ai/`\\\\n- `storage/`\\\\n\\\\n### Suggested durable concepts\\\\n- Session\\\\n- Workflow stage\\\\n- Event log\\\\n- Selected genre\\\\n- Selected tone\\\\n- Story brief\\\\n- Pitch batch + selected pitch\\\\n- Character batch + selected character sheet\\\\n- Beat sheet\\\\n- Story setup preferences\\\\n- Outline / chapter or scene plan\\\\n- Continuity bible\\\\n- Composition job\\\\n- Composition segment\\\\n- Audio job\\\\n- Asset record\\\\n\\\\n## Real-Time and Long-Running Work\\\\n\\\\nTreat composition and audio generation as **durable background jobs**, not request-thread work.\\\\n\\\\n- The browser should be able to refresh without losing the job.\\\\n- The UI should receive live progress updates.\\\\n- The backend should own current truth about progress.\\\\n- A separate worker process is strongly preferred.\\\\n- Use PostgreSQL-backed durable job records.\\\\n- Persist partial outputs frequently enough that resume is trustworthy.\\\\n\\\\n## Chat and UI Bridge Rules\\\\n\\\\nThe product must support true bidirectional interaction.\\\\n\\\\n### Chat-to-UI\\\\nA user message can propose actions like:\\\\n- select a tone\\\\n- regenerate pitches\\\\n- choose a pitch\\\\n- adjust character traits\\\\n- soften the midpoint\\\\n- shorten the story target\\\\n- pause writing\\\\n- change narration speed\\\\n\\\\n### UI-to-Chat\\\\nA direct UI action should appear in the chat history as a compact structured summary, for example:\\\\n- \\u201cSelected genre: Quest Fantasy\\u201d\\\\n- \\u201cUpdated target runtime: ~12 minutes\\u201d\\\\n- \\u201cAccepted revised beat sheet\\u201d\\\\n\\\\n### Safety rule\\\\nThe model can **propose** actions, but a deterministic policy layer should decide whether they are valid in the current session state.\\\\n\\\\n## Save The Cat Expectations\\\\n\\\\nUse the Save The Cat method as the backbone of planning.\\\\n\\\\n- The beat sheet should be explicit, editable, and stored as structured data.\\\\n- The composition stage should write against the beat sheet and the detailed outline derived from it.\\\\n- Bedtime adaptation matters: the low points can be emotionally meaningful without becoming harsh or distressing.\\\\n- The final story should still feel like a transformation story, not just a string of nice scenes.\\\\n\\\\n## Genre and Tone Expectations\\\\n\\\\nUse the included research docs to seed:\\\\n- a curated genre list\\\\n- per-genre tone options\\\\n- bedtime-suitable arc notes\\\\n- tone descriptors that can guide UI copy and AI prompting\\\\n\\\\nDo **not** label tones with living or copyrighted-author names. Use generic tone labels and descriptors.\\\\n\\\\n## Audio Expectations\\\\n\\\\nNarration must be treated as a real product feature, not a side demo.\\\\n\\\\n- Segment audio generation so it is resumable\\\\n- Estimate length heuristically before generation\\\\n- Support voice selection\\\\n- Support speed controls\\\\n- Support optional background music\\\\n- Keep music subordinate to narration clarity\\\\n- Produce a final compiled audio artifact\\\\n- Keep intermediate and final artifacts trackable through durable metadata\\\\n\\\\n## Export Expectations\\\\n\\\\nAt minimum, the user must be able to get:\\\\n- final story text in the app\\\\n- final audio in the app\\\\n- downloadable `.docx`\\\\n- downloadable final audio file\\\\n\\\\n## Developer Experience and Quality Bar\\\\n\\\\nFavor:\\\\n- typed interfaces\\\\n- boring, explicit service boundaries\\\\n- migrations\\\\n- tests around durable state\\\\n- visible logs\\\\n- simple scripts for local dev\\\\n\\\",\\\"exit_code\\\":0,\\\"status\\\":\\\"completed\\\"}}\\nprompts/00-project-charter.codex.jsonlines:38:{\\\"type\\\":\\\"item.completed\\\",\\\"item\\\":{\\\"id\\\":\\\"item_20\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"command_execution\\\",\\\"command\\\":\\\"/bin/zsh -lc \\\\\\\"sed -n '1,240p' docs/product-brief.md\\\\\\\"\\\",\\\"aggregated_output\\\":\\\"# Product Brief\\\\n\\\\n## Product Summary\\\\n\\\\nStoryteller is a session-based bedtime story creation studio. It helps a user move from a loose story idea to a finished written story and finished narration audio, with the ability to leave and come back later without losing progress.\\\\n\\\\nThe first meaningful screen is the sessions home. It must foreground past sessions, including both in-progress and completed stories, so resume and revisit are the default behaviors rather than an afterthought.\\\\n\\\\n## User Experience Principles\\\\n\\\\n- Bedtime-first: stories should support calm endings, emotional repair, and low-friction read-aloud use.\\\\n- Guided, not opaque: users move through explicit workflow stages instead of one giant prompt box.\\\\n- Bidirectional control: chat can suggest UI actions, and UI actions must be echoed back into chat.\\\\n- Durable by default: progress survives refreshes, restarts, and long-running generation work.\\\\n- Local-first development: the full stack should run locally through Docker Compose with persistent infrastructure.\\\\n\\\\n## End-to-End Workflow\\\\n\\\\nThe product must support this ordered flow:\\\\n\\\\n1. Genre selection from a curated genre list.\\\\n2. Tone selection from options preconfigured for the chosen genre.\\\\n3. Story setup through a free-form brief describing the desired story.\\\\n4. Story pitches generated by Gemini, with selection, refinement, or regeneration.\\\\n5. Character sheet generation, again with selection and refinement.\\\\n6. Save-the-Cat beat sheet generation and editing.\\\\n7. Story setup preferences for soft targets such as word count, runtime, and chapters.\\\\n8. Composition in segments with visible progress, typewriter-like output, and interruptibility.\\\\n9. Audio configuration and audio generation, including voice and speed controls plus optional background music.\\\\n10. Finalize, where the user can read, listen, and download story and audio artifacts.\\\\n\\\\n## Core Product Behaviors\\\\n\\\\n### Sessions and Resume\\\\n\\\\n- Sessions are durable backend entities.\\\\n- A user can reopen a session from any stage.\\\\n- In-progress and completed sessions both appear on the home screen.\\\\n\\\\n### Workspace Layout\\\\n\\\\n- Desktop layout uses two panes.\\\\n- Left pane is the chat workspace, about one-third width.\\\\n- Right pane is the main workflow UI, about two-thirds width.\\\\n\\\\n### Chat and UI Bridge\\\\n\\\\n- User chat can propose structured actions such as selecting a tone or refining beats.\\\\n- The model may propose actions, but a deterministic backend policy layer decides whether each action is valid for the session's current stage.\\\\n- Direct UI actions must create compact chat-visible summaries for auditability and replay.\\\\n\\\\n### Composition Experience\\\\n\\\\n- Story writing happens in segments.\\\\n- Progress is visible and should feel meaningfully live.\\\\n- The system should periodically summarize what it is writing in chat.\\\\n- Users can interrupt, redirect, and request rewrites.\\\\n\\\\n### Audio Experience\\\\n\\\\n- Narration is a first-class feature, not a demo extra.\\\\n- Audio generation is segmented and resumable.\\\\n- The app estimates likely runtime before generation starts.\\\\n- Final audio should be playable in-app and downloadable.\\\\n\\\\n## Non-Negotiable Technical Constraints\\\\n\\\\n- Frontend: React, Vite, TypeScript\\\\n- Backend: Python, FastAPI\\\\n- Structured persistence: PostgreSQL\\\\n- Object storage in local development: file-backed GCS emulator\\\\n- Local orchestration: Docker Compose\\\\n- Secrets: local `secrets.yaml`, excluded from git\\\\n- AI model family: Gemini 3.1, with backend-owned adapters and centralized model configuration\\\\n\\\\n## Deliverable Expectations\\\\n\\\\nThe finished product should let a user:\\\\n\\\\n- create and revise a bedtime story plan\\\\n- generate and edit a complete story\\\\n- generate, play, and download narration audio\\\\n- download the story as `.docx`\\\\n- resume work from prior sessions without losing context\\\\n\\\",\\\"exit_code\\\":0,\\\"status\\\":\\\"completed\\\"}}\\nprompts/00-project-charter.codex.jsonlines:39:{\\\"type\\\":\\\"item.completed\\\",\\\"item\\\":{\\\"id\\\":\\\"item_19\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"command_execution\\\",\\\"command\\\":\\\"/bin/zsh -lc \\\\\\\"sed -n '1,260p' docs/architecture-overview.md\\\\\\\"\\\",\\\"aggregated_output\\\":\\\"# Architecture Overview\\\\n\\\\n## System Picture\\\\n\\\\nStoryteller is a full-stack application with a browser client, a backend-owned workflow engine, durable relational state, durable object storage, and resumable background jobs.\\\\n\\\\n```text\\\\nReact + Vite client\\\\n        |\\\\n        v\\\\nFastAPI API layer\\\\n        |\\\\n        +--> domain services and policy layer\\\\n        |         |\\\\n        |         +--> AI adapters for planning, composition, and narration\\\\n        |         |\\\\n        |         +--> repositories for sessions, workflow state, jobs, and event log\\\\n        |\\\\n        +--> background workers for composition and audio generation\\\\n                  |\\\\n                  +--> PostgreSQL for durable structured state\\\\n                  +--> file-backed GCS emulator for artifacts and intermediate blobs\\\\n```\\\\n\\\\n## Why Gemini Calls Must Stay on the Backend\\\\n\\\\nAll Gemini access belongs on the server side for four reasons:\\\\n\\\\n1. Secrets control: provider credentials live in local `secrets.yaml` and must never enter the browser.\\\\n2. Policy enforcement: chat-to-UI actions and workflow transitions need deterministic server validation before the model can change session state.\\\\n3. Durable orchestration: prompts, structured outputs, retries, and model selection need to be coordinated with persistent session data and job records.\\\\n4. Provider flexibility: keeping Gemini behind backend adapters lets the app keep a stable internal interface while model IDs, structured output tactics, or narration providers evolve.\\\\n\\\\nThe frontend should only call the backend's API and subscribe to backend-owned progress events.\\\\n\\\\n## Why Composition and Audio Must Use Resumable Server-Side Jobs\\\\n\\\\nComposition and narration are long-running operations that cannot safely live inside request threads or browser memory. They need server-side jobs because:\\\\n\\\\n- a user must be able to refresh the page or return later without losing progress\\\\n- partial story text and audio segments need durable checkpoints\\\\n- progress updates need a single source of truth that both chat and UI can observe\\\\n- retries, cancellation, and resume logic need explicit job state rather than transient in-memory state\\\\n\\\\nThe durable model should include job records, segment records, asset metadata, and an event log that can reconstruct session progress after interruption.\\\\n\\\\n## Intended Backend Shape\\\\n\\\\nThe target backend should separate concerns explicitly:\\\\n\\\\n- `api/`: HTTP routes and websocket endpoints\\\\n- `settings/`: environment and secrets loading\\\\n- `db/`: database engine, migrations, and persistence setup\\\\n- `models/`: typed domain models and persistence schemas\\\\n- `repositories/`: database access for sessions, events, jobs, and assets\\\\n- `services/`: workflow logic and policy enforcement\\\\n- `ai/`: Gemini planning, composition, and narration adapters\\\\n- `worker/`: background job execution for writing and audio\\\\n- `storage/`: object storage abstraction over the local GCS emulator\\\\n\\\\n## Durable Domain Concepts\\\\n\\\\nThe system should persist the following concepts as first-class records:\\\\n\\\\n- Session\\\\n- Workflow stage\\\\n- Event log\\\\n- Selected genre\\\\n- Selected tone\\\\n- Story brief\\\\n- Pitch batch and selected pitch\\\\n- Character batch and selected character sheet\\\\n- Beat sheet\\\\n- Story setup preferences\\\\n- Outline or chapter plan\\\\n- Continuity bible\\\\n- Composition job and segments\\\\n- Audio job and segments\\\\n- Asset metadata\\\\n\\\\n## Current Repository State\\\\n\\\\nThe repository currently contains an initial scaffold:\\\\n\\\\n- `frontend/`: Vite React app\\\\n- `backend/`: FastAPI app\\\\n- `docker-compose.yml`: local frontend, backend, and browser QA services\\\\n- `tools/webapp-qa/`: containerized browser automation support\\\\n\\\\nPostgreSQL, the file-backed GCS emulator, background workers, and most domain layers are still planned work. This document records the required direction so later prompts can extend the scaffold without changing the architectural contract.\\\\n\\\",\\\"exit_code\\\":0,\\\"status\\\":\\\"completed\\\"}}\\nprompts/00-project-charter.codex.jsonlines:40:{\\\"type\\\":\\\"item.completed\\\",\\\"item\\\":{\\\"id\\\":\\\"item_21\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"command_execution\\\",\\\"command\\\":\\\"/bin/zsh -lc \\\\\\\"sed -n '1,240p' README.md\\\\\\\"\\\",\\\"aggregated_output\\\":\\\"# Storyteller\\\\n\\\\nStoryteller is a local-first, full-stack app for creating bedtime stories from first idea to finished text and finished narration audio. The product is session-based: the first meaningful screen is a past-sessions view where a user can resume work in progress, reopen a completed story, or start a new session.\\\\n\\\\nThis repository currently contains the first scaffold for that system. The project charter in this README and the supporting docs define the product and architecture that later prompts will implement.\\\\n\\\\n## Product Vision\\\\n\\\\nThe app should feel like a guided bedtime story studio, not a generic prompt box. A user should be able to:\\\\n\\\\n- See past sessions first and continue where they left off.\\\\n- Collaborate through both chat and direct UI controls.\\\\n- Move through a structured planning workflow before long-form writing starts.\\\\n- Watch story composition and audio generation progress in real time.\\\\n- Return later to read, listen, download, or revise completed work.\\\\n\\\\nThe tone of the product should stay calm, readable, and trustworthy. Wonder, mystery, and adventure are welcome, but bedtime suitability is a hard requirement: emotional stakes should resolve safely and the ending should feel restful.\\\\n\\\\n## Required Story Workflow\\\\n\\\\nThe application is being built around this ordered workflow:\\\\n\\\\n1. Genre selection\\\\n2. Tone selection\\\\n3. Story setup / free-form brief\\\\n4. Story pitches\\\\n5. Character sheet\\\\n6. Save-the-Cat beat sheet\\\\n7. Story setup preferences such as word count, runtime, and chapters\\\\n8. Composition\\\\n9. Audio configuration and audio generation\\\\n10. Finalize / read / listen / download\\\\n\\\\nEach stage must be durable, resumable, and editable. Chat messages can propose actions in the workflow, and direct UI actions must also be reflected back into the session chat log as compact summaries.\\\\n\\\\n## Fixed Technical Decisions\\\\n\\\\nThese choices are not optional for this project:\\\\n\\\\n- Frontend: React + Vite + TypeScript\\\\n- Backend: Python + FastAPI\\\\n- Structured data: PostgreSQL\\\\n- Blob storage: file-backed GCS emulator in local development\\\\n- Local orchestration: Docker Compose\\\\n- Secrets handling: local `secrets.yaml`, never committed to git\\\\n- AI access: Gemini 3.1 family behind backend-owned adapters and services\\\\n\\\\nTwo architectural rules follow from those constraints:\\\\n\\\\n- The browser must never hold provider secrets or call Gemini directly.\\\\n- Long-running story composition and narration generation must be durable background jobs with resumable server-side state.\\\\n\\\\nMore detail is in [docs/product-brief.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/product-brief.md) and [docs/architecture-overview.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/architecture-overview.md).\\\\n\\\\n## Local Development Expectations\\\\n\\\\nThe repo is intended to run locally with Docker Compose. At the current scaffold stage:\\\\n\\\\n- `frontend/` contains a Vite React app served on `http://localhost:8566`\\\\n- `backend/` contains a FastAPI app served on `http://localhost:8565`\\\\n- `tools/webapp-qa/` contains the browser automation container used for local UI verification\\\\n\\\\nStart the current stack with:\\\\n\\\\n```bash\\\\ndocker compose up --build\\\\n```\\\\n\\\\nThe current scaffold does not yet include PostgreSQL or the file-backed GCS emulator, but both are required parts of the target system and will be added through later prompt work. `secrets.yaml` is already gitignored and reserved for local-only credentials.\\\\n\\\\n## Repository Shape\\\\n\\\\n- `frontend/`: React + Vite client application\\\\n- `backend/`: FastAPI application and future domain services\\\\n- `docs/`: product and architecture notes\\\\n- `prompts/`: sequential build prompts and task summaries\\\\n- `tools/`: local QA and developer tooling\\\\n\\\\n## What Success Looks Like\\\\n\\\\nA new engineer should be able to open this repository and quickly understand:\\\\n\\\\n- the first screen is the past-sessions home for resume, edit, and create flows\\\\n- the story workflow is staged and ordered\\\\n- the final product writes stories and generates narration audio durably\\\\n- the backend owns AI access, long-running jobs, and persistent state\\\\n\\\",\\\"exit_code\\\":0,\\\"status\\\":\\\"completed\\\"}}\\nprompts/00-project-charter.codex.jsonlines:41:{\\\"type\\\":\\\"item.started\\\",\\\"item\\\":{\\\"id\\\":\\\"item_22\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"command_execution\\\",\\\"command\\\":\\\"/bin/zsh -lc \\\\\\\"python - <<'PY'\\\\nfrom pathlib import Path\\\\nfiles = {\\\\n    'README.md': Path('README.md').read_text(),\\\\n    'docs/product-brief.md': Path('docs/product-brief.md').read_text(),\\\\n    'docs/architecture-overview.md': Path('docs/architecture-overview.md').read_text(),\\\\n}\\\\nrequired_stages = [\\\\n    'Genre selection',\\\\n    'Tone selection',\\\\n    'Story setup',\\\\n    'Story pitches',\\\\n    'Character sheet',\\\\n    'Save-the-Cat beat sheet',\\\\n    'Story setup preferences',\\\\n    'Composition',\\\\n    'Audio configuration and audio generation',\\\\n    'Finalize / read / listen / download',\\\\n]\\\\nprint('files_present:', all(Path(p).exists() for p in files))\\\\nprint('readme_mentions_past_sessions_early:', 'first meaningful screen is a past-sessions view' in files['README.md'])\\\\nfor stage in required_stages:\\\\n    print(stage, stage in files['README.md'])\\\\nchecks = {\\\\n    'react_vite_typescript': all(term in files['README.md'] for term in ['React + Vite + TypeScript']),\\\\n    'fastapi_backend': 'Python + FastAPI' in files['README.md'],\\\\n    'postgres': 'PostgreSQL' in files['README.md'],\\\\n    'gcs_emulator': 'file-backed GCS emulator' in files['README.md'],\\\\n    'docker_compose': 'Docker Compose' in files['README.md'],\\\\n    'secrets_yaml': 'secrets.yaml' in files['README.md'],\\\\n    'backend_gemini_note': 'Gemini' in files['docs/architecture-overview.md'] and 'backend' in files['docs/architecture-overview.md'],\\\\n    'resumable_jobs_note': 'resumable server-side jobs' in files['docs/architecture-overview.md'],\\\\n}\\\\nfor name, ok in checks.items():\\\\n    print(name, ok)\\\\nPY\\\\\\\"\\\",\\\"aggregated_output\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"exit_code\\\":null,\\\"status\\\":\\\"in_progress\\\"}}\\nprompts/00-project-charter.codex.jsonlines:42:{\\\"type\\\":\\\"item.completed\\\",\\\"item\\\":{\\\"id\\\":\\\"item_22\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"command_execution\\\",\\\"command\\\":\\\"/bin/zsh -lc \\\\\\\"python - <<'PY'\\\\nfrom pathlib import Path\\\\nfiles = {\\\\n    'README.md': Path('README.md').read_text(),\\\\n    'docs/product-brief.md': Path('docs/product-brief.md').read_text(),\\\\n    'docs/architecture-overview.md': Path('docs/architecture-overview.md').read_text(),\\\\n}\\\\nrequired_stages = [\\\\n    'Genre selection',\\\\n    'Tone selection',\\\\n    'Story setup',\\\\n    'Story pitches',\\\\n    'Character sheet',\\\\n    'Save-the-Cat beat sheet',\\\\n    'Story setup preferences',\\\\n    'Composition',\\\\n    'Audio configuration and audio generation',\\\\n    'Finalize / read / listen / download',\\\\n]\\\\nprint('files_present:', all(Path(p).exists() for p in files))\\\\nprint('readme_mentions_past_sessions_early:', 'first meaningful screen is a past-sessions view' in files['README.md'])\\\\nfor stage in required_stages:\\\\n    print(stage, stage in files['README.md'])\\\\nchecks = {\\\\n    'react_vite_typescript': all(term in files['README.md'] for term in ['React + Vite + TypeScript']),\\\\n    'fastapi_backend': 'Python + FastAPI' in files['README.md'],\\\\n    'postgres': 'PostgreSQL' in files['README.md'],\\\\n    'gcs_emulator': 'file-backed GCS emulator' in files['README.md'],\\\\n    'docker_compose': 'Docker Compose' in files['README.md'],\\\\n    'secrets_yaml': 'secrets.yaml' in files['README.md'],\\\\n    'backend_gemini_note': 'Gemini' in files['docs/architecture-overview.md'] and 'backend' in files['docs/architecture-overview.md'],\\\\n    'resumable_jobs_note': 'resumable server-side jobs' in files['docs/architecture-overview.md'],\\\\n}\\\\nfor name, ok in checks.items():\\\\n    print(name, ok)\\\\nPY\\\\\\\"\\\",\\\"aggregated_output\\\":\\\"files_present: True\\\\nreadme_mentions_past_sessions_early: True\\\\nGenre selection True\\\\nTone selection True\\\\nStory setup True\\\\nStory pitches True\\\\nCharacter sheet True\\\\nSave-the-Cat beat sheet True\\\\nStory setup preferences True\\\\nComposition True\\\\nAudio configuration and audio generation True\\\\nFinalize / read / listen / download True\\\\nreact_vite_typescript True\\\\nfastapi_backend True\\\\npostgres True\\\\ngcs_emulator True\\\\ndocker_compose True\\\\nsecrets_yaml True\\\\nbackend_gemini_note True\\\\nresumable_jobs_note False\\\\n\\\",\\\"exit_code\\\":0,\\\"status\\\":\\\"completed\\\"}}\\nprompts/00-project-charter.codex.jsonlines:59:{\\\"type\\\":\\\"item.completed\\\",\\\"item\\\":{\\\"id\\\":\\\"item_32\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"agent_message\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"Added the project charter docs at [README.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/README.md), [docs/product-brief.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/product-brief.md), and [docs/architecture-overview.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/architecture-overview.md). The README now calls out the past-sessions-first home screen early, lists the full staged workflow in order, and documents the fixed stack and local development expectations. The architecture note records the backend-only Gemini boundary and the requirement for resumable server-side composition/audio jobs.\\\\n\\\\nVerification was docs-focused: I manually reviewed all three files, ran a Python acceptance check covering file presence, first-screen wording, ordered workflow, fixed stack documentation, backend Gemini rationale, resumable jobs rationale, and sessions-home coverage in the product brief, and ran `git diff --check`, which passed. No tests, builds, browser checks, or screenshots were applicable because this task was documentation-only.\\\\n\\\\nI created the requested checkpoint commit `feat(prompt-00): project charter`, and the required reviewer summary file was written last at [prompts/00-project-charter.summary.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/prompts/00-project-charter.summary.md).\\\"}}\\nbackend/tests/test_event_log_service.py:13:from app.services.event_log import SessionEventLogService\\nbackend/tests/test_event_log_service.py:41:    event_log = SessionEventLogService(db_session)\\nbackend/tests/test_event_log_service.py:67:    event_log.record_chat_message(\\nbackend/tests/test_event_log_service.py:145:    event_log = SessionEventLogService(db_session)\\nbackend/tests/test_event_log_service.py:155:    event_log.record_chat_message(\\nprompts/36-conversation-memory-summaries.md:7:Create a compact memory mechanism so the system can retain story decisions and conversation context across long sessions without stuffing full chat history into every prompt.\\nprompts/36-conversation-memory-summaries.md:22:- Later model calls can stay grounded without receiving the entire raw chat log.\\nprompts/24-design-tokens-and-accessibility-foundation.summary.md:52:intentionally boring and composable rather than app-specific.\\nprompts/24-design-tokens-and-accessibility-foundation.summary.md:184:without re-creating the same surface style for chat entries, toasts, or\\ndocs/chat-to-ui-actions.schema.json:28:    \\\"chat_to_ui_action\\\": {\\ndocs/chat-to-ui-actions.schema.json:2089:    \\\"chat_to_ui_action_batch\\\": {\\nbackend/tests/test_chat_action_contracts.py:14:    get_chat_to_ui_action_default_policy,\\nbackend/tests/test_chat_action_contracts.py:15:    get_chat_to_ui_action_schema_bundle,\\nbackend/tests/test_chat_action_contracts.py:20:def test_chat_to_ui_action_contract_supports_stage_specific_actions() -> None:\\nbackend/tests/test_chat_action_contracts.py:73:def test_chat_to_ui_action_contract_rejects_confirm_first_actions_without_confirmation() -> None:\\nbackend/tests/test_chat_action_contracts.py:97:def test_chat_to_ui_action_contract_rejects_missing_structured_values() -> None:\\nbackend/tests/test_chat_action_contracts.py:119:def test_chat_to_ui_action_contract_rejects_job_stage_mismatch() -> None:\\nbackend/tests/test_chat_action_contracts.py:145:        get_chat_to_ui_action_default_policy(ChatToUIActionType.SELECT_PITCH)\\nbackend/tests/test_chat_action_contracts.py:149:        get_chat_to_ui_action_default_policy(ChatToUIActionType.OPEN_FINALIZE_VIEW)\\nbackend/tests/test_chat_action_contracts.py:154:def test_chat_to_ui_action_schema_bundle_matches_checked_in_schema_file() -> None:\\nbackend/tests/test_chat_action_contracts.py:156:        Path(__file__).resolve().parents[2] / \\\"docs\\\" / \\\"chat-to-ui-actions.schema.json\\\"\\nbackend/tests/test_chat_action_contracts.py:159:    assert json.loads(schema_path.read_text()) == get_chat_to_ui_action_schema_bundle()\\nprompts/11-postgres-schema-and-migrations.summary.md:77:The relational design intentionally preserves the workflow model established in prompt 10:\\nprompts/11-postgres-schema-and-migrations.summary.md:93:- table creation order is intentional\\nprompts/11-postgres-schema-and-migrations.summary.md:306:My first `migrations/env.py` implementation would only use the Alembic config URL or else fall back to `get_settings()`. During live PostgreSQL verification that failed because the migration command only needs a database URL, but the full app settings loader also requires Gemini and GCS settings.\\nbackend/tests/test_realtime_contracts.py:126:            \\\"type\\\": \\\"chat.message\\\",\\nbackend/tests/test_realtime_contracts.py:138:                \\\"message_id\\\": \\\"chat-15\\\",\\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:23:        |         +--> repositories for sessions, workflow state, jobs, and event log\\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:31:## Why Gemini Calls Must Stay on the Backend\\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:33:All Gemini access belongs on the server side for four reasons:\\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:36:2. Policy enforcement: chat-to-UI actions and workflow transitions need deterministic server validation before the model can change session state.\\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:38:4. Provider flexibility: keeping Gemini behind backend adapters lets the app keep a stable internal interface while model IDs, structured output tactics, or narration providers evolve.\\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:48:- progress updates need a single source of truth that both chat and UI can observe\\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:51:The durable model should include job records, segment records, asset metadata, and an event log that can reconstruct session progress after interruption.\\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:63:- `ai/`: Gemini planning, composition, and narration adapters\\nfrontend/src/styles/index.css:183:.workspace-chat-pane__status,\\nfrontend/src/styles/index.css:184:.workspace-chat-entry p,\\nfrontend/src/styles/index.css:185:.workspace-chat-entry time,\\nfrontend/src/styles/index.css:186:.workspace-chat-composer p,\\nfrontend/src/styles/index.css:461:.workspace-chat-transcript {\\nfrontend/src/styles/index.css:1221:.workspace-chat-composer__header strong,\\nfrontend/src/styles/index.css:1268:.workspace-chat-composer,\\nfrontend/src/styles/index.css:1269:.workspace-chat-pane__status,\\nfrontend/src/styles/index.css:1597:.workspace-pane--chat {\\nfrontend/src/styles/index.css:1621:.workspace-chat-pane__heading {\\nfrontend/src/styles/index.css:1625:.workspace-chat-pane__status {\\nfrontend/src/styles/index.css:1631:.workspace-chat-transcript {\\nfrontend/src/styles/index.css:1639:.workspace-chat-entry {\\nfrontend/src/styles/index.css:1643:.workspace-chat-entry--user {\\nfrontend/src/styles/index.css:1647:.workspace-chat-bubble {\\nfrontend/src/styles/index.css:1658:.workspace-chat-entry--assistant .workspace-chat-bubble {\\nfrontend/src/styles/index.css:1668:.workspace-chat-entry--user .workspace-chat-bubble {\\nfrontend/src/styles/index.css:1678:.workspace-chat-entry--system .workspace-chat-bubble {\\nfrontend/src/styles/index.css:1683:.workspace-chat-entry--action_echo .workspace-chat-bubble {\\nfrontend/src/styles/index.css:1688:.workspace-chat-entry__meta {\\nfrontend/src/styles/index.css:1705:.workspace-chat-entry time {\\nfrontend/src/styles/index.css:1710:.workspace-chat-entry p {\\nfrontend/src/styles/index.css:1715:.workspace-chat-composer {\\nfrontend/src/styles/index.css:1723:.workspace-chat-composer__header,\\nfrontend/src/styles/index.css:1724:.workspace-chat-composer__footer {\\nfrontend/src/styles/index.css:1731:.workspace-chat-composer__header strong {\\nfrontend/src/styles/index.css:1736:.workspace-chat-composer__footer {\\nfrontend/src/styles/index.css:2058:  .workspace-pane--chat {\\nfrontend/src/styles/index.css:2063:  .workspace-chat-transcript {\\nfrontend/src/styles/index.css:2101:  .workspace-chat-composer__header,\\nfrontend/src/styles/index.css:2102:  .workspace-chat-composer__footer {\\nprompts/19-data-layer-integration-tests.summary.md:52:These are intentionally behavior-shaped rather than implementation-shaped. Each test crosses real persistence boundaries by reopening SQLAlchemy sessions after commits and, for storage, by reading back bytes and metadata from the fake GCS server.\\nprompts/19-data-layer-integration-tests.summary.md:148:- event log persistence\\nprompts/19-data-layer-integration-tests.summary.md:163:- the 5 skipped tests are the new integration tests, intentionally skipped in the default fast path\\nprompts/19-data-layer-integration-tests.summary.md:228:I intentionally did not build bucket-deletion cleanup into the harness. The suite isolates storage writes through unique object paths and isolates relational state with disposable databases and table truncation. That is simpler and reliable with the current fake-GCS setup, which is enough for this prompt\\u2019s durability focus.\\nprompts/00-project-charter.yolopilot.md:6:- Compact event log: `/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/prompts/00-project-charter.yolopilot.jsonlines`\\nprompts/00-project-charter.yolopilot.md:188:    prompts/30-chat-to-ui-action-schema.md\\nprompts/00-project-charter.yolopilot.md:204:    prompts/45-pitch-refinement-via-chat.md\\nprompts/00-project-charter.yolopilot.md:215:    prompts/25-chat-window-foundation.md\\nprompts/00-project-charter.yolopilot.md:218:    prompts/49-beat-sheet-refinement-ui-and-chat.md\\nprompts/00-project-charter.yolopilot.md:221:    prompts/47-character-refinement-via-chat.md\\nprompts/00-project-charter.yolopilot.md:239:    prompts/31-intent-parser-service.md\\nprompts/00-project-charter.yolopilot.md:244:    prompts/33-action-echoes-in-chat.md\\nprompts/00-project-charter.yolopilot.md:260:    prompts/35-chat-commands-and-quick-actions.md\\nprompts/00-project-charter.yolopilot.md:333:    - Add a short architecture note describing why all Gemini calls must happen on the backend and why long-running composition and audio jobs need resumable server-side state.\\nprompts/00-project-charter.yolopilot.md:381:       - **Left pane:** chat window, about one-third of the desktop width.\\nprompts/00-project-charter.yolopilot.md:384:       - The user can type in chat, and the system can translate those messages into UI actions.\\nprompts/00-project-charter.yolopilot.md:385:       - The user can act directly in the UI, and those actions should be reflected in the chat log and in durable session state.\\nprompts/00-project-charter.yolopilot.md:425:       - Gemini generates multiple candidate pitches.\\nprompts/00-project-charter.yolopilot.md:426:       - The user can select one, ask for alternatives, or refine via chat.\\nprompts/00-project-charter.yolopilot.md:428:       - Gemini generates multiple candidate character sheets.\\nprompts/00-project-charter.yolopilot.md:429:       - The user can select or refine via chat.\\nprompts/00-project-charter.yolopilot.md:431:       - Gemini generates a Save-the-Cat beat sheet for the selected plan.\\nprompts/00-project-charter.yolopilot.md:432:       - The user can refine the beats via chat or UI.\\nprompts/00-project-charter.yolopilot.md:441:       - The agent should periodically post chat summaries of what it is writing.\\nprompts/00-project-charter.yolopilot.md:475:    - Use the **Gemini 3.1 family** for text/planning/composition workloads\\nprompts/00-project-charter.yolopilot.md:480:      - planning/classification/intent parsing\\nprompts/00-project-charter.yolopilot.md:551:    A direct UI action should appear in the chat history as a compact structured summary, for example:\\nprompts/00-project-charter.yolopilot.md:1118:    - Bidirectional control: chat can suggest UI actions, and UI actions must be echoed back into chat.\\nprompts/00-project-charter.yolopilot.md:1129:    4. Story pitches generated by Gemini, with selection, refinement, or regeneration.\\nprompts/00-project-charter.yolopilot.md:1148:    - Left pane is the chat workspace, about one-third width.\\nprompts/00-project-charter.yolopilot.md:1153:    - User chat can propose structured actions such as selecting a tone or refining beats.\\nprompts/00-project-charter.yolopilot.md:1155:    - Direct UI actions must create compact chat-visible summaries for auditability and replay.\\nprompts/00-project-charter.yolopilot.md:1161:    - The system should periodically summarize what it is writing in chat.\\nprompts/00-project-charter.yolopilot.md:1179:    - AI model family: Gemini 3.1, with backend-owned adapters and centralized model configuration\\nprompts/00-project-charter.yolopilot.md:1220:            |         +--> repositories for sessions, workflow state, jobs, and event log\\nprompts/00-project-charter.yolopilot.md:1228:    ## Why Gemini Calls Must Stay on the Backend\\nprompts/00-project-charter.yolopilot.md:1230:    All Gemini access belongs on the server side for four reasons:\\nprompts/00-project-charter.yolopilot.md:1233:    2. Policy enforcement: chat-to-UI actions and workflow transitions need deterministic server validation before the model can change session state.\\nprompts/00-project-charter.yolopilot.md:1235:    4. Provider flexibility: keeping Gemini behind backend adapters lets the app keep a stable internal interface while model IDs, structured output tactics, or narration providers evolve.\\nprompts/00-project-charter.yolopilot.md:1245:    - progress updates need a single source of truth that both chat and UI can observe\\nprompts/00-project-charter.yolopilot.md:1248:    The durable model should include job records, segment records, asset metadata, and an event log that can reconstruct session progress after interruption.\\nprompts/00-project-charter.yolopilot.md:1260:    - `ai/`: Gemini planning, composition, and narration adapters\\nprompts/00-project-charter.yolopilot.md:1319:    - Collaborate through both chat and direct UI controls.\\nprompts/00-project-charter.yolopilot.md:1341:    Each stage must be durable, resumable, and editable. Chat messages can propose actions in the workflow, and direct UI actions must also be reflected back into the session chat log as compact summaries.\\nprompts/00-project-charter.yolopilot.md:1353:    - AI access: Gemini 3.1 family behind backend-owned adapters and services\\nprompts/00-project-charter.yolopilot.md:1357:    - The browser must never hold provider secrets or call Gemini directly.\\nprompts/00-project-charter.yolopilot.md:1430:    'backend_gemini_note': 'Gemini' in files['docs/architecture-overview.md'] and 'backend' in files['docs/architecture-overview.md'],\\nprompts/00-project-charter.yolopilot.md:1469:        'backend_gemini_note': 'Gemini' in files['docs/architecture-overview.md'] and 'backend' in files['docs/architecture-overview.md'],\\nprompts/00-project-charter.yolopilot.md:1512:    'backend_gemini_note': 'Gemini' in files['docs/architecture-overview.md'] and 'backend' in files['docs/architecture-overview.md'],\\nprompts/00-project-charter.yolopilot.md:1551:        'backend_gemini_note': 'Gemini' in files['docs/architecture-overview.md'] and 'backend' in files['docs/architecture-overview.md'],\\nprompts/00-project-charter.yolopilot.md:1969:    Added the project charter docs at [README.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/README.md), [docs/product-brief.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/product-brief.md), and [docs/architecture-overview.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/architecture-overview.md). The README now calls out the past-sessions-first home screen early, lists the full staged workflow in order, and documents the fixed stack and local development expectations. The architecture note records the backend-only Gemini boundary and the requirement for resumable server-side composition/audio jobs.\\nprompts/00-project-charter.yolopilot.md:1971:    Verification was docs-focused: I manually reviewed all three files, ran a Python acceptance check covering file presence, first-screen wording, ordered workflow, fixed stack documentation, backend Gemini rationale, resumable jobs rationale, and sessions-home coverage in the product brief, and ran `git diff --check`, which passed. No tests, builds, browser checks, or screenshots were applicable because this task was documentation-only.\\nbackend/tests/integration/test_data_layer.py:17:    EventLogEntry,\\nbackend/tests/integration/test_data_layer.py:26:from app.services.event_log import SessionEventLogService\\nbackend/tests/integration/test_data_layer.py:167:                select(EventLogEntry)\\nbackend/tests/integration/test_data_layer.py:168:                .where(EventLogEntry.session_id == created.id)\\nbackend/tests/integration/test_data_layer.py:169:                .order_by(EventLogEntry.sequence_number.asc())\\nbackend/tests/integration/test_data_layer.py:206:        event_log = SessionEventLogService(session)\\nbackend/tests/integration/test_data_layer.py:215:        event_log.record_chat_message(\\nbackend/tests/integration/test_data_layer.py:231:        event_log = SessionEventLogService(session)\\ndocs/system-diagram.md:7:    Browser[\\\"Browser UI<br/>React + Vite<br/>sessions home, chat pane, workflow pane\\\"]\\ndocs/system-diagram.md:13:    Gemini[\\\"Gemini adapters<br/>planning, composition, narration\\\"]\\ndocs/system-diagram.md:28:    Worker -->|\\\"planning, composition, TTS calls\\\"| Gemini\\ndocs/system-diagram.md:29:    API -. \\\"backend-owned model config and policy\\\" .-> Gemini\\ndocs/system-diagram.md:34:- The browser never calls Gemini directly.\\nprompts/03-fastapi-scaffold.yolopilot.md:6:- Compact event log: `/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/prompts/03-fastapi-scaffold.yolopilot.jsonlines`\\nprompts/03-fastapi-scaffold.yolopilot.md:177:    ./prompts/30-chat-to-ui-action-schema.md\\nprompts/03-fastapi-scaffold.yolopilot.md:196:    ./prompts/45-pitch-refinement-via-chat.md\\nprompts/03-fastapi-scaffold.yolopilot.md:210:    ./prompts/25-chat-window-foundation.md\\nprompts/03-fastapi-scaffold.yolopilot.md:214:    ./prompts/49-beat-sheet-refinement-ui-and-chat.md\\nprompts/03-fastapi-scaffold.yolopilot.md:217:    ./prompts/47-character-refinement-via-chat.md\\nprompts/03-fastapi-scaffold.yolopilot.md:236:    ./prompts/31-intent-parser-service.md\\nprompts/03-fastapi-scaffold.yolopilot.md:243:    ./prompts/33-action-echoes-in-chat.md\\nprompts/03-fastapi-scaffold.yolopilot.md:261:    ./prompts/35-chat-commands-and-quick-actions.md\\nprompts/03-fastapi-scaffold.yolopilot.md:9274:    - Collaborate through both chat and direct UI controls.\\nprompts/03-fastapi-scaffold.yolopilot.md:9296:    Each stage must be durable, resumable, and editable. Chat messages can propose actions in the workflow, and direct UI actions must also be reflected back into the session chat log as compact summaries.\\nprompts/03-fastapi-scaffold.yolopilot.md:9308:    - AI access: Gemini 3.1 family behind backend-owned adapters and services\\nprompts/03-fastapi-scaffold.yolopilot.md:9312:    - The browser must never hold provider secrets or call Gemini directly.\\nprompts/03-fastapi-scaffold.yolopilot.md:9496:    - Added placeholder READMEs in the major folders so a new engineer can infer intent without reading the prompt pack first:\\nprompts/03-fastapi-scaffold.yolopilot.md:9788:      - The visual language is intentionally calmer and more product-specific than the generic template.\\nprompts/03-fastapi-scaffold.yolopilot.md:9844:    The current router is intentionally small. To add another route later, extend `src/app/router.tsx`:\\nprompts/03-fastapi-scaffold.yolopilot.md:9996:    - I intentionally ran this before starting the backend to confirm the frontend still boots in isolation.\\nprompts/03-fastapi-scaffold.yolopilot.md:10202:            |         +--> repositories for sessions, workflow state, jobs, and event log\\nprompts/03-fastapi-scaffold.yolopilot.md:10210:    ## Why Gemini Calls Must Stay on the Backend\\nprompts/03-fastapi-scaffold.yolopilot.md:10212:    All Gemini access belongs on the server side for four reasons:\\nprompts/03-fastapi-scaffold.yolopilot.md:10215:    2. Policy enforcement: chat-to-UI actions and workflow transitions need deterministic server validation before the model can change session state.\\nprompts/03-fastapi-scaffold.yolopilot.md:10217:    4. Provider flexibility: keeping Gemini behind backend adapters lets the app keep a stable internal interface while model IDs, structured output tactics, or narration providers evolve.\\nprompts/03-fastapi-scaffold.yolopilot.md:10227:    - progress updates need a single source of truth that both chat and UI can observe\\nprompts/03-fastapi-scaffold.yolopilot.md:10230:    The durable model should include job records, segment records, asset metadata, and an event log that can reconstruct session progress after interruption.\\nprompts/03-fastapi-scaffold.yolopilot.md:10242:    - `ai/`: Gemini planning, composition, and narration adapters\\nprompts/03-fastapi-scaffold.yolopilot.md:15286:    Verification passed with backend pytest, `compileall`, live local startup plus `curl` checks, Docker Compose startup with the new `/health` healthcheck, and the existing browser smoke spec. The required reviewer summary was written last to [03-fastapi-scaffold.summary.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/prompts/03-fastapi-scaffold.summary.md). Current intentional limit: database wiring is still a scaffold and reports `not-configured` until later prompts.\\nprompts/15-event-log-and-audit-trail.yolopilot.jsonlines:6:{\\\"color\\\": \\\"green\\\", \\\"emoji\\\": \\\"\\\\ud83d\\\\udcac\\\", \\\"event_type\\\": \\\"Agent Message\\\", \\\"message\\\": \\\"I\\\\u2019m inspecting the current backend/domain shape first so I can add the event log in the existing patterns instead of inventing a parallel architecture. After that I\\\\u2019ll map where session mutations happen, add the append-only model/helpers...\\\", \\\"raw_event\\\": {\\\"item\\\": {\\\"id\\\": \\\"item_0\\\", \\\"text\\\": \\\"I\\\\u2019m inspecting the current backend/domain shape first so I can add the event log in the existing patterns instead of inventing a parallel architecture. After that I\\\\u2019ll map where session mutations happen, add the append-only model/helpers, wire event writes into those flows, and verify with tests.\\\", \\\"type\\\": \\\"agent_message\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"item.completed\\\"}, \\\"task_display_context\\\": {\\\"event_number\\\": 6, \\\"prompt_index\\\": 16, \\\"prompt_name\\\": \\\"15 \\\\u2014 Event Log and Audit Trail\\\", \\\"prompt_total\\\": 100}, \\\"timestap\\\": \\\"2026-03-31T23:35:51-07:00\\\"}\\nprompts/15-event-log-and-audit-trail.yolopilot.jsonlines:10:{\\\"color\\\": \\\"cyan\\\", \\\"emoji\\\": \\\"\\\\ud83d\\\\udee0\\\\ufe0f\\\", \\\"event_type\\\": \\\"Command Finished\\\", \\\"message\\\": \\\"completed, exit 0: /bin/zsh -lc 'rg --files'\\\", \\\"raw_event\\\": {\\\"item\\\": {\\\"aggregated_output\\\": \\\"secrets.example.yaml\\\\nprompts/00-project-charter.codex.jsonlines\\\\nprompts/36-conversation-memory-summaries.md\\\\nprompts/11-postgres-schema-and-migrations.summary.md\\\\nprompts/99-release-checklist-and-future-roadmap.md\\\\nprompts/11-postgres-schema-and-migrations.yolopilot.jsonlines\\\\nprompts/44-pitch-generation-pipeline.md\\\\nprompts/10-domain-model-and-state-machine.codex.jsonlines\\\\nprompts/11-postgres-schema-and-migrations.yolopilot.md\\\\nprompts/08-repo-quality-tooling.yolopilot.jsonlines\\\\nprompts/04-docker-compose-foundation.codex.jsonlines\\\\nprompts/05-backend-settings-and-secrets-loading.summary.md\\\\nprompts/08-repo-quality-tooling.codex.jsonlines\\\\nprompts/42-story-setup-brief-form.md\\\\nprompts/07-developer-bootstrap-scripts.md\\\\nprompts/13-storage-abst