/events.py), an append/read repository in [events.py](/Users/kevin/code/sto...\\\", \\\"raw_event\\\": {\\\"item\\\": {\\\"id\\\": \\\"item_87\\\", \\\"text\\\": \\\"Implemented the prompt 15 event/audit layer end to end. The backend now has a typed event taxonomy in [events.py](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/app/models/events.py), an append/read repository in [events.py](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/app/repositories/events.py), a higher-level logging service in [event_log.py](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/app/services/event_log.py), and `SessionService` wiring in [sessions.py](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/app/services/sessions.py) so session creation and stage transitions emit durable, versioned events and update `last_event_id` pointers on affected stage snapshots. I also documented the taxonomy in [event-taxonomy.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/event-taxonomy.md) and wrote the required reviewer summary in [15-event-log-and-audit-trail.summary.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/prompts/15-event-log-and-audit-trail.summary.md).\\\\n\\\\nVerification: `pytest backend/tests/test_event_log_service.py backend/tests/test_session_service.py` passed (`10 passed`), `pytest backend/tests` passed (`36 passed`), and `ruff check backend/app backend/tests` passed. No browser checks or screenshots were run because this prompt only changed backend/domain code. I made a checkpoint commit for the implementation as `9ca7cc4` (`feat(prompt-15): event log and audit trail`).\\\", \\\"type\\\": \\\"agent_message\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"item.completed\\\"}, \\\"task_display_context\\\": {\\\"event_number\\\": 195, \\\"prompt_index\\\": 16, \\\"prompt_name\\\": \\\"15 \\\\u2014 Event Log and Audit Trail\\\", \\\"prompt_total\\\": 100}, \\\"timestap\\\": \\\"2026-03-31T23:54:02-07:00\\\"}\\nprompts/15-event-log-and-audit-trail.yolopilot.jsonlines:196:{\\\"color\\\": \\\"bright_black\\\", \\\"emoji\\\": \\\"\\\\u2753\\\", \\\"event_type\\\": \\\"Unkown Event\\\", \\\"message\\\": \\\"{ \\\\\\\"item\\\\\\\": { \\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"item_42\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"items\\\\\\\": [ { \\\\\\\"completed\\\\\\\": false, \\\\\\\"text\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"Add event taxonomy models plus repository/service helpers for append-only session events and history reads\\\\\\\" }, { \\\\\\\"completed\\\\\\\": false, \\\\\\\"text\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"Wire event logging into...\\\", \\\"raw_event\\\": {\\\"item\\\": {\\\"id\\\": \\\"item_42\\\", \\\"items\\\": [{\\\"completed\\\": false, \\\"text\\\": \\\"Add event taxonomy models plus repository/service helpers for append-only session events and history reads\\\"}, {\\\"completed\\\": false, \\\"text\\\": \\\"Wire event logging into current session mutations and expose backend session history loading\\\"}, {\\\"completed\\\": false, \\\"text\\\": \\\"Expand tests and docs for event taxonomy, replay assumptions, and helper usage\\\"}, {\\\"completed\\\": false, \\\"text\\\": \\\"Run targeted verification, commit checkpoints, and write the required task summary file\\\"}], \\\"type\\\": \\\"todo_list\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"item.completed\\\"}, \\\"task_display_context\\\": {\\\"event_number\\\": 196, \\\"prompt_index\\\": 16, \\\"prompt_name\\\": \\\"15 \\\\u2014 Event Log and Audit Trail\\\", \\\"prompt_total\\\": 100}, \\\"timestap\\\": \\\"2026-03-31T23:54:02-07:00\\\"}\\nprompts/00-project-charter.summary.md:13:  - Documented the fixed technical choices from the brief: React + Vite + TypeScript, Python + FastAPI, PostgreSQL, a file-backed GCS emulator, Docker Compose, backend-owned Gemini access, and `secrets.yaml` excluded from git.\\nprompts/00-project-charter.summary.md:18:  - Captured the bedtime-story positioning, the sessions-first UX requirement, the staged workflow, the two-pane workspace, and the chat/UI bridge rules.\\nprompts/00-project-charter.summary.md:22:  - Explained why Gemini calls must stay on the backend.\\nprompts/00-project-charter.summary.md:38:  - The frontend must never hold provider secrets or call Gemini directly.\\nprompts/00-project-charter.summary.md:39:  - Gemini usage should be isolated behind backend adapters for planning, long-form generation, and narration.\\nprompts/00-project-charter.summary.md:43:  - PostgreSQL-backed job records, segment records, and event logs are part of the intended design.\\nprompts/00-project-charter.summary.md:48:  - `docs/` now holds product and architecture intent.\\nprompts/00-project-charter.summary.md:59:  - Example: if you are building pitch generation or beat-sheet editing, the product brief defines the required stage order and the expectation that chat and UI actions mirror each other.\\nprompts/00-project-charter.summary.md:63:  - Example: if you later add Gemini integration, this doc already sets the boundary that secrets stay in `secrets.yaml` and model access stays behind backend services.\\nprompts/00-project-charter.summary.md:118:- The only Gemini-related changes were architectural documentation notes.\\nprompts/11-postgres-schema-and-migrations.yolopilot.jsonlines:9:{\\\"color\\\": \\\"cyan\\\", \\\"emoji\\\": \\\"\\\\ud83d\\\\udee0\\\\ufe0f\\\", \\\"event_type\\\": \\\"Command Finished\\\", \\\"message\\\": \\\"completed, exit 0: /bin/zsh -lc 'pwd && rg --files .'\\\", \\\"raw_event\\\": {\\\"item\\\": {\\\"aggregated_output\\\": \\\"/Users/kevin/code/storyteller\\\\n./secrets.example.yaml\\\\n./prompts/00-project-charter.codex.jsonlines\\\\n./prompts/36-conversation-memory-summaries.md\\\\n./prompts/99-release-checklist-and-future-roadmap.md\\\\n./prompts/11-postgres-schema-and-migrations.yolopilot.jsonlines\\\\n./prompts/44-pitch-generation-pipeline.md\\\\n./prompts/10-domain-model-and-state-machine.codex.jsonlines\\\\n./prompts/11-postgres-schema-and-migrations.yolopilot.md\\\\n./prompts/08-repo-quality-tooling.yolopilot.jsonlines\\\\n./prompts/04-docker-compose-foundation.codex.jsonlines\\\\n./prompts/05-backend-settings-and-secrets-loading.summary.md\\\\n./prompts/0