nlines:204:{\\\"type\\\":\\\"item.completed\\\",\\\"item\\\":{\\\"id\\\":\\\"item_109\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"file_change\\\",\\\"changes\\\":[{\\\"path\\\":\\\"/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/prompts/25-chat-window-foundation.summary.md\\\",\\\"kind\\\":\\\"add\\\"}],\\\"status\\\":\\\"completed\\\"}}\\nprompts/25-chat-window-foundation.codex.jsonlines:205:{\\\"type\\\":\\\"item.completed\\\",\\\"item\\\":{\\\"id\\\":\\\"item_110\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"agent_message\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"Implemented prompt 25 end to end. The left workspace pane is now a real chat surface with typed `assistant` / `user` / `system` / `action_echo` messages, timestamps, a multiline composer with submit handling, loading and disabled states, and a scroll-stable transcript backed by the session runtime store. The main wiring lives in [SessionChatPane.tsx](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/frontend/src/features/session/chat/SessionChatPane.tsx), [sessionChat.ts](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/frontend/src/features/session/chat/sessionChat.ts), and [SessionWorkspacePage.tsx](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/frontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.tsx). I also added a reusable [TextArea](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/frontend/src/shared/ui/primitives.tsx) primitive and committed the code checkpoint as `40b66cc` with message `feat(prompt-25): chat window foundation`.\\\\n\\\\nVerification passed:\\\\n- `npm run lint`\\\\n- `npm test -- src/features/session/chat/SessionChatPane.test.tsx src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.test.tsx src/features/session/sessionRuntimeStore.test.ts src/shared/ui/primitives.test.tsx` (`14` tests passed)\\\\n- `npm test` (`24` tests passed)\\\\n- `npm run build`\\\\n- Browser QA against the running Compose app, with screenshots at [chat-foundation-before-desktop.png](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/.artifacts/chat-foundation-before-desktop.png), [chat-foundation-after-desktop.png](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/.artifacts/chat-foundation-after-desktop.png), and [chat-foundation-after-mobile.png](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/.artifacts/chat-foundation-after-mobile.png)\\\\n\\\\nThe required reviewer summary was written last to [25-chat-window-foundation.summary.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/prompts/25-chat-window-foundation.summary.md).\\\"}}\\nprompts/25-chat-window-foundation.codex.jsonlines:206:{\\\"type\\\":\\\"item.completed\\\",\\\"item\\\":{\\\"id\\\":\\\"item_27\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"todo_list\\\",\\\"items\\\":[{\\\"text\\\":\\\"Inspect current workspace shell, runtime state, and visual QA workflow to identify the clean integration point for the chat pane foundation\\\",\\\"completed\\\":true},{\\\"text\\\":\\\"Implement typed session chat state and reusable chat pane components, then wire them into the workspace page with local submit behavior and role-specific rendering\\\",\\\"completed\\\":false},{\\\"text\\\":\\\"Add or update automated tests covering chat message rendering, composer behavior, and workspace integration\\\",\\\"completed\\\":false},{\\\"text\\\":\\\"Run frontend verification including lint, tests, build, git checkpoint commit, and screenshot-based visual QA through the compose app\\\",\\\"completed\\\":false},{\\\"text\\\":\\\"Write the required reviewer-facing markdown summary file as the final action\\\",\\\"completed\\\":false}]}}\\nfrontend/src/features/session/SessionStageEditorPreview.tsx:116:            description=\\\"When chat asks for more options, regenerated cards can land here without collapsing the layout rhythm.\\\"\\ndocs/product-brief.md:13:- Bidirectional control: chat can suggest UI actions, and UI actions must be echoed back into chat.\\ndocs/product-brief.md:24:4. Story pitches generated by Gemini, with selection, refinement, or regeneration.\\ndocs/product-brief.md:43:- Left pane is the chat workspace, about one-third width.\\ndocs/product-brief.md:48:- User chat can propose structured actions such as selecting a tone or refining beats.\\ndocs/product-brief.md:50:- Direct UI actions must create compact chat-visible summaries for auditability and replay.\\ndocs/product-brief.md:56:- The system should periodically summarize what it is writing in chat.\\ndocs/product-brief.md:74:- AI model family: Gemini 3.1, with backend-owned adapters and centralized model configuration\\nfrontend/src/features/session/sessionRuntimeStore.test.ts:142:      chat: {\\nfrontend/src/features/session/sessionRuntimeStore.test.ts:215:  it('adds chat and action-echo events to the transcript while confirming correlated actions', () => {\\nfrontend/src/features/session/sessionRuntimeStore.test.ts:253:      type: 'chat.message',\\nfrontend/src/features/session/sessionRuntimeStore.test.ts:268:        message_id: 'chat-16',\\nfrontend/src/features/session/sessionRuntimeStore.test.ts:272:        source: 'chat',\\nfrontend/src/features/session/sessionRuntimeStore.test.ts:286:    expect(store.getState().chat.messages).toEqual([\\nfrontend/src/features/session/sessionRuntimeStore.test.ts:292:        id: 'chat-16',\\nbackend/tests/test_db_models.py:17:    EventLogEntry,\\nbackend/tests/test_db_models.py:73:        completion_event = EventLogEntry(\\ndocs/README.md:10:- `chat-to-ui-actions.md`: proposed action contract, action catalog, and default confirmation policy\\ndocs/README.md:11:- `chat-to-ui-actions.schema.json`: machine-readable schema bundle for chat-to-UI proposed actions\\ndocs/README.md:17:- `system-diagram.md`: one-page runtime diagram for browser, API, worker, storage, and Gemini flows\\nbackend/app/services/__init__.py:10:from app.services.event_log import SessionEventLogService\\nbackend/app/services/__init__.py:40:    \\\"SessionEventLogService\\\",\\nfrontend/src/features/session/live/sessionRealtimeClient.test.ts:154:      type: 'chat.message',\\nfrontend/src/features/session/live/sessionRealtimeClient.test.ts:169:        message_id: 'chat-20',\\nfrontend/src/features/session/live/sessionRealtimeClient.test.ts:173:        source: 'chat',\\nfrontend/src/fe